{
  "texts": [
    "Head Movement is the most restrictive, so it is exclusively used in the most limited 'Passive' types of experience.",
    "Regarding the results of 6DoF, it can be seen that Teleport Locomotion is the most widely used type of interaction.",
    "This result is expected, as it has been one of the most common types of locomotion in iVR over recent years, as Prithul pointed out in his teleportation review [159].",
    "Regarding all the iVR 6DoF experiences, Explorative experiences are the most varied interaction types, which may because they are the most common in the earlier years of the study when taxonomies and locomotion systems were more general and less specific [160].",
    "In Explorative interaction, there is an increase in the use of Teleport locomotion, probably because these experiences are more modern and there is a need to teleport over long distances [159]."
  ]
}